For a variety of projects I've got on, I needed a set of human heads to add to models I intend to sculpt for 3D printing. I couldn't find any I like, so have made up a collection of heads I've created by scratch sculpting, using Blender Add-ons, etc. None are 'stock' generation. Each has been scratch sculpted, re-sculpted from add-on generated blank faces, modified, re-shaped etc by me to meet the needs of my projects for 28mm - 32mm scale miniatures. 

I really struggled to find any free base heads I could use as a starting block to model onto, so am putting these here as a resource for any other amateur enthusiast designers like me who need a start until our scratch-sculpting talents get to where they need to be!

If you do use them in your own projects, would love to see them.

Remixed some of my paleolithic people to make some units for Grudge. What is Grudge? It’s a crunchy little (but still one-sheet) mini-agnostic narrative campaign that Ill Gotten Games is designing for their CRUX: Universal Wargaming rules. It plays in parts as a bloody familial feud and farming sim. Find out more on the IGG Patreon or through DutchMogul here on Thingiverse.

I call these four the Wulfstrael Family, composed of Mother Wulfstrael (who carries a knife and does the butchering.) Old Man Wulfstrael, who dispatches livestock with his trusty hammer, and their two daughters, Hilda and Editha, who hunt game with their bows. The family generally deals in meat and hides, raising cattle, sheep and pigs, but also tanning and preparing pelts and hides for trade.

Psionic fungaloid warriors? Sure, why not! I wanted to design some 15mm scale infantry models that would print with little difficulty, and these guys seem to work well for that.

These characters were designed for our sci-fantasy tabletop RPG, [Wayfarer: Things Beyond Wonder](http://www.illgottengames.net/wayfarer/) and for our modular wargaming system, [Wayfarer Tactics](http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1227640). If you want to print a 28mm scale version, just scale it up by 180%.

We've set up a [Patreon page](https://www.patreon.com/illgottengames) for anyone who's interested in helping to fund us so we can keep making free and open sourced games like Pocket-Tactics, Wayfarer Tactics. and others, not to mention the growing catalog of gaming miniatures that you can use for whatever you want! (Psst... we take requests and commissions...)

Enjoy!

He's much smaller than Metal Pig, but still fairly large depending on what scale games you play (assuming he'd be for that in the first place). The pics are him alongside some commonly used 15mm and 28mm scale models respectively.



Not a lot of changes made to the original model other than the head and scaling, though there;s some minor design alterations.
